posts.body:
The absolute worst is that there's no /tg/ board on this.  
Chrow and all the other infinite fa/tg/uys, I will miss you most of all.

I legitimately would love to seed, but currently we are running with a free VPN service with a limited data plan.  If I succeed in escaping NEETdom I'll put upgrading\swapping to a good torrent friendly service with my first paycheck.  
Hoping that we're still around that long, of course.

posts.subject: PDF/Share Thread - Rebuild Edition
posts.body:
It's what Chrow would have wanted us to do at least.

So Request, Read, enjoy the end of the world.
Last Thread Archive:
http://archive.is/5xOKs
This the thread from MAY, unfortunately it seems difficult to get the last share thread, unless some other brave soul was able to archive it some other fashion.  In the meantime you're going to need to go to the site through TOR and wait like 10 minutes for it to load then browse that.

I've finally been trying out Sunless Sea, and it's OK.  Been meaning to actually play System Shock start to finish so I might as well get on with that.
I did have Sekiro, but I haven't been enjoying it too much to be honest.  It just feels like its stuck halfway between wanting to be another Soulsborne but also trying to be Tenchu and it suffers because it can't really make up its mind.

Okay I just have to say it I don't care if this board is dead but sweet Jesus going back to 4chan was not the right answer, that version of /tg/ is so fucking trash.  Template threads everywhere, nonstop shitposts in each thread, 'ironic' defense of Paizos fluff writing and others.  I'd sooner give up all image boards waiting for 8chan to come back than try and adapt to that mess.

Man, am I glad that my writeup distinctly told me to use TOR and a free VPN service.
Of course said VPN service (Tunnel Bear) is in the US and 5 EYES compliant if they really wanted to nab me they could.  
Does anyone know good torrent friendly VPN services?  For some reason I just don't like NordVPN, I see a lot of youtube (((Personalities))) shilling it and that immediately weirds me out.  I was actually thinking Anonine but I just don't know.

Can someone feed me a (You)?  I just tried the TOR fix and I want confirmation ebfore I try and make posts anywhere else.

 I can see you anon.
